      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0354P1-05704'>
        <a name='S6CV0354P1_20000727_WH_30'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-lidington' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0354P1_20000727_WH_30' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Lidington' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-lidington" title="Mr David Lidington">Mr. Lidington</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I am saying, as the Minister well knows, that the country must pay what it can afford. The Government have been reluctant to release the detailed figures underlying the headlines, which the Chancellor published last week. I have tabled questions to Home Office Ministers to dig out from them how they envisage the money being spent. So far I have been
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_275wh' title='Col. 275WH &mdash; HC Deb 27 July 2000 vol 354 c275WH' name='column_275wh' href='#column_275wh' rel='bookmark'>275WH</a>
            stonewalled, but I live in hope that I will strike a golden seam and unexpectedly find information from Ministers.</p><p>
            I was speaking about the systems for bidding and financial planning. The point about priorities not being simply about how much money is available but about how effectively it will be spent is made crisply on page 96 of the Home Office report. Inspectors say that few of the partnerships have clear financial plans. The report states:
            <q>Even where there was a partnership budget &#x2026; it was rarely aligned to priorities.</q>
            The inspectors state that to the best of their knowledge only one local authority, the royal borough of Kensington and Chelsea, is known to have carried out a full costing of its community safety plan. So, whatever the Minister promises for this year, next year or four years' time, and even if, on the most optimistic assumption, the money is given to crime reduction partnerships, if that money is to make a difference to the lives of constituents, it is essential to put in place arrangements for financial planning and for the setting of priorities. According to the inspectors, that is demonstrably lacking.</p><p>
            Another area of concern is the sharing of data between the different agencies involved in partnerships. The inspectors found what they described as too much caution and concern among senior managers, which was primarily due to their lack of confidence that the powers in crime and disorder legislation would be sufficient defence in a court action against personal liability under the <a href="/acts/data-protection-act-1998">Data Protection Act 1998</a>. Given that finding, there is a clear need for the Government to publish a circular that will reassure people that they can exchange data.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0354P1-05705'>
        <a name='S6CV0354P1_20000727_WH_31'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-steve-mccabe' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0354P1_20000727_WH_31' title='Link to this speech by Mr Steve McCabe' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-steve-mccabe" title="Mr Steve McCabe">Mr. McCabe</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            Does the hon. Gentleman accept that, although that has been a genuine concern, a solution has come from the police and other agencies establishing proper protocols for sharing information? A current excellent example in the west midlands is the policy for tackling the problem of abandoned vehicles, which is based on the information sharing that has resulted from the protocol established 12 months ago.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0354P1-05706'>
        <a name='S6CV0354P1_20000727_WH_32'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mrs-gwyneth-dunwoody' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0354P1_20000727_WH_32' title='Link to this speech by Mrs Gwyneth Dunwoody' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
